I"1	<p>A lot of people have noticed shit tons of ferferral spam from semalt.com and their various other domains.</p>

<p>Itâ€™s fucking annoying.</p>

<p>I found a short S3 policy <a href="http://admium.tumblr.com/">here</a> that blocked semalt.com from accessing static sites hosted on S3 and adapted it to include larger list of all know semalt.com domains as well as some from my logs.</p>

<p>I created a repo for the policy and you can find it <a href="https://github.com/chrisanthropic/S3-semalt-blocklist-policy">here</a>.</p>

<h3 id="about">About</h3>
<p>The policy blocks variations and subdomains of the given sites: ie <code class="highlighter-rouge">semalt.com</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">semalt.com/anything</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">randomstringsemalt.com</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">www.semalt.com</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">www.semalt.com/anything</code></p>

<h3 id="use">Use</h3>
<p>Copy and past the contents of <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chrisanthropic/S3-semalt-blocklist-policy/master/Policy.txt">blocklist.txt</a> to your S3 bucket policy and change the two instances of <code class="highlighter-rouge">YOURBUCKETNAME</code> to the actual name of your bucket.</p>

